2.00	Hampton_House_(Chicago,_Illinois)	Hampton House (Chicago, Illinois)	The Hampton House is a residential condominium located in the Hyde Park neighborhood of Chicago, Illinois on the property that once housed the Hyde Park House, a hotel built by Hyde Park founder Paul Cornell in the 1850s. The property was originally named the Sisson Hotel when constructed in 1918.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/f/fc/20061022_Hampton_House.JPG/250px-20061022_Hampton_House.JPG
